column10: Cyclist ringing a loud bell speed though intersection, failing to stop or yield to other cars crossing though intersection. Cars had to slam on brakes to avoid very obnoxious and brazen attitude of as he weaved around cars, almost hitting me

Intersection traffic causes non stop honking with cars not following laws (full stop, speeding) or common courtesy. I live off the intersection and probably hear or view 2-5 near misses on a daily basis.
The stop signs on Blair Road at Pinetree Terrace are routinely and repeatedly run through by drivers on Blair Road.  About one in ten drivers actually stops at the stop signs.
